>>what is argocd , how argocd is going to authenticate kubernetes cluster ?

Argo CD is a GitOps Continuous Delivery (CD) tool for Kubernetes.
Argo CD continuously watches a Git repository and makes sure the Kubernetes cluster exactly matches what is defined in Git
Desired state lives in Git
Actual state lives in Kubernetes
Argo CD compares both and syncs them
Pulls Kubernetes manifests from Git
Applies them to the cluster
Continuously compares Git vs Cluster
Shows drift in UI/CLI
Auto‑syncs or manual syncs
Provides audit & rollback
Argo CD authenticates to Kubernetes using Kubernetes ServiceAccounts and RBAC
 It uses ServiceAccount authentication
ServiceAccount is:
An identity for applications (pods)
Used by pods to talk to Kubernetes API

Argo CD Pod Starts
Argo CD runs in namespace argocd
Each component has a ServiceAccount

ServiceAccount Token Is Mounted

Argo CD Calls Kubernetes API
Example calls:

Create Deployment
Update Service
Delete Pod

Kubernetes API Server Validates Token

 RBAC Decides What Argo CD Can Do


Argo CD Pod
   |
   |-- ServiceAccount Token
   |
Kubernetes API Server
   |
   |-- RBAC Check
   |
Cluster Resources


what is meant by push mechanism and pull mechanism ?

Push vs Pull describes who initiates the action
– the sender (push) or the receiver (pull)
In a push mechanism, the source actively sends data or changes to the destination.
🔹 Sender decides when and what to send

In a pull mechanism, the destination actively asks for data or changes.
🔹 Receiver decides when to fetch
🔹 Sender only provides data when asked

Argo CD checks Git periodically
If Git changed → Argo CD pulls changes
Applies changes to cluster

✅ Git never pushes to cluster
✅ Cluster state controlled by Argo CD




